problem_prompt: Approach the following question the way someone with a PhD in mathematics would. What is the remainder when $2001 \cdot 2002 \cdot 2003 \cdot 2004 \cdot 2005$ is divided by 19?
solution: Reducing each factor modulo 19 first, we see that $2001 \cdot 2002 \cdot 2003 \cdot 2004 \cdot 2005 \equiv 6 \cdot 7 \cdot 8 \cdot 9 \cdot 10 \equiv 30240 \equiv \boxed{11} \pmod{19}$.
gpt_response:
To find the remainder when $2001 \cdot 2002 \cdot 2003 \cdot 2004 \cdot 2005$ is divided by 19, we can first simplify the expression by considering each number modulo 19. 

First, we find the remainders of each number modulo 19:
$2001 \equiv 10 \pmod{19}$
$2002 \equiv 11 \pmod{19}$
$2003 \equiv 12 \pmod{19}$
$2004 \equiv 13 \pmod{19}$
$2005 \equiv 14 \pmod{19}$

Now, we can find the product of these remainders:
$(10 \cdot 11 \cdot 12 \cdot 13 \cdot 14) \mod 19$

To simplify the product, we can reduce each factor modulo 19:
$10 \cdot 11 \cdot 12 \cdot 13 \cdot 14 \equiv (10 \cdot 11) \cdot (12 \cdot 13) \cdot 14 \equiv 8 \cdot 9 \cdot 14 \equiv 112 \cdot 14 \equiv 3 \cdot 14 \equiv 42 \equiv 4 \pmod{19}$

Therefore, the remainder when $2001 \cdot 2002 \cdot 2003 \cdot 2004 \cdot 2005$ is divided by 19 is 4.
